{"lemma":"عَقْرَبَيْ","slug":"عَقْرَبَيْ","root":"ع.ق.ر.ب","root_slug":"ع-ق-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29933","n29935","n29940"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"scorpion","examples":[{"text":"الْعَقْرَب (al-ʕaqrab, “Scorpio”)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Scorpius, a constellation of the zodiac"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Scorpio, the zodiac sign for the scorpion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hour hand of a clock, so named from its ending in two prongs"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʕaḳrab-. Compare Jewish Palestinian Aramaic עַקְרַבָּא (ʿaqraḇā), Classical Syriac ܥܶܩܰܪܒܳܐ (ʿeqarbā), Hebrew עַקְרָב (ʿaqrāḇ), Ugaritic 𐎓𐎖𐎗𐎁 (ʿqrb), Ge'ez ዐቅረብ (ʿäḳräb); attested as a Semitic word since Akkadian 𒀝𒊏𒁍 (aqrabu)."},"ipa":["/ʕaq.rab/","/ʕaɡ.rab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29933","headword_ar":"عَقْرَبَ","root":"Eqrb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He twisted, wreathed, curled, curved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing. (MA.)       -A2-  [And, accord. to Freytag,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He imitated the scorpion in acting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but for this he names no authority; and I doubt its correctness: see the next paragraph.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29935","headword_ar":"عَقْرَبٌ","root":"Eqrb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scorpion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain venomous reptile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) the word is masc. (TA) and it is fem., (S, O, K, TA,) generally the latter; (T, Msb, TA;) but is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, O, Msb, TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqorubaAnN","text_ar":"عُقْرُبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, O, Msb, K, TA,) accord. to some, (O,) when one desires to denote it in a corroborative manner, (Msb, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqorub~aAnN","text_ar":"عُقْرُبَّانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also; (K;) or these two words are syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabapN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, O, Msb, K,) sometimes, (T, Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabaA='u","text_ar":"عَقْرَبَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is imperfectly decl.; (S, O, K;) or these two words and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the “ Tahreer et-Tembeeh, ” all denote the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqorubaAnN","text_ar":"عُقْرُبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female"},{"kind":"text","text":"are called only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) and of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqorubaAnN","text_ar":"عُقْرُبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is said by IB, on the authority of AHát, that it does not signify the male of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaArib","text_ar":"عَقَارِب"},{"kind":"text","text":", but [as expl. below] “ a certain creeping thing, having long legs: ” (TA:) IJ says that you may drop the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":", and say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqorur~aAn","text_ar":"عُقْرُرَّان","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, TA:) and an instance occurs of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqoraAbN","text_ar":"عَقْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a coll. gen. n., in the following verse:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aEuw*u biA@ll~`hi mina AlEaqoraAbi\n                      \n                     \n                        Aal$~aAy^ilaAti Euqada AlA^a*onaAbi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I seek protection by God from the scorpions raising the joints of the tails"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"here is said to be inserted for the purpose of what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_i$obaAE","text_ar":"الاـِشْبَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MF, from the “ Mukhtasar el-Bayán: ”) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$Ay^lAt","text_ar":"الشايلات"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied as an epithet to a sing. n. because this is used as a coll. gen. n.: (M voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabosabN","text_ar":"سَبْسَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAribu","text_ar":"عَقَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) ―         -b2-  And [hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaqorabu","text_ar":"العَقْرَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain sign of the Zodiac,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, O, K,) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Scorpio,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] to which belong the Mansions of the Moon called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~awolapu","text_ar":"الشَّوْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqalobu","text_ar":"القَلْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ikoliylu","text_ar":"الاـِكْلِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~ubaAnayaAni","text_ar":"الزُّبَانَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, TA. [See these words, and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iybaAnu","text_ar":"شِيبَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAzilu Alqamari","text_ar":"مَنَازِلُ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nzl","text_ar":"نزل"},{"kind":"text","text":". It should also be observed that the Arabs extended the figure of this constellation (as they did that of Leo) far beyond the limits that we assign to it.]) ―         -b3-  [Hence, likewise,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a sandal, (O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the form of the reptile of this name."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqorabap","text_ar":"عَقْرَبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaited, and having a buckle at its extremity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the crupper of a horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, is bound to the saddle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b5-  And the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAribu","text_ar":"عَقَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Malicious and mischievous misrepresentations, calumnies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slanders."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu latadib~u EaqaAribuhu","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَتَدِبُّ عَقَارِبُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily his malicious and mischievous misrepresentations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"creep along:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he traduces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defames, people behind their backs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"otherwise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) And the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dab~ato EaqaAribuhu","text_ar":"دَبَّتْ عَقَارِبُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used to signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His downy hair crept"},{"kind":"text","text":"[along his cheeks]. (MF.) ―         -b6-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Reproaches for benefits conferred:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying of En-Nábighah,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"EalaY~a liEamorKw niEomapN baEoda niEomapK\n                      \n                     \n                        liwaAlidihi layosato bi*aAti EaqaAribi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I owe unto 'Amr favour after favour, for his father, not accompanied by reproaches for benefits conferred"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b7-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hardships, severities, difficulties, troubles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distresses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAribu","text_ar":"عَقَارِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~itaA='i","text_ar":"الشِّتَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hardships, severities,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of winter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the intense cold thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqorabu Al$~itaA='i","text_ar":"عَقْرَبُ الشِّتَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to IB,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the assault, and intense cold, of winter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N *uw","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAriba","text_ar":"عَقَارِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An uneasy life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a life in which is evil and roughness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-  See also the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":["TA","K","S","O","Lth","T","Msb","L"]},{"entry_id":"n29940","headword_ar":"عُقْرُبٌّ","root":"Eqrb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}